        <num>CC 1962</num>
        <heading>1962.  Threat of exercising a right</heading>
        <content>
          <p>Art. 1962.  Threat of exercising a right
A threat of doing a lawful act or a threat of exercising a right does not constitute duress.
A threat of doing an act that is lawful in appearance only may constitute duress.</p>
        </content>
